<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3155067" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="1"><variable id="print_tofit"><link href="text/simpress/guide/print_tofit.xhp" name="Printing a Slide to Fit a Paper Size">Printing a Slide to Fit a Paper Size</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3154704" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="3">You can reduce the size of a slide when you print, so that the slide can fit on a printed page.</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3154658" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="4">Open the document that you want to print.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3145384" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">In <emph>Normal View</emph>, choose <emph>Format - Page</emph>, and then click the <emph>Page</emph> tab.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3148871" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="6">In <emph>Layout settings </emph>area, select the <emph>Fit object to paper format</emph> check box.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3153811" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="7">In the <emph>Paper format</emph> area, select a <emph>Format</emph>.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3150431" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="8">Click <emph>OK</emph>. The slide is resized to fit the printed page, while maintaining the relative positions of the objects on the slide.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
